OL,3,CPensioners left frustrated over lack
OL,4,Cof decision on alleged 'double tax'
OL,6,FJersey pensioners are frustrated that
OL,7,Ftheir concerns over being taxed twice
OL,8,Fare not being acted on.
OL,10,FIt comes as a petition, that received
OL,11,Fmore than 5,000 signatures, called for
OL,12,Fthe States of Jersey to debate whether
OL,13,Fdouble-taxing pensions should be
OL,14,Fabolished.
OL,16,FThe petition stated: "All employed
OL,17,Fpersons are obliged by law to pay
OL,18,Fsocial security contributions.
OL,19,FContributions are not deducted from
OL,20,Fgross pay for taxation purposes.
