OL,6,FDeputy Barbara Ward says: "If you've
OL,7,Fgot 5,000 people that are voting for
OL,8,Fsomething, that's over 6% of the
OL,9,Fpopulation.
OL,11,F"We can't ignore them."
OL,13,FConnetable Karen Shenton-Stone, who
OL,14,Fhas political responsibility over the
OL,15,Fpetitions process, has also encouraged
OL,16,Fpeople who see petitions reaching the
OL,17,Fthousands to contact their local
OL,18,Frepresentative to see if they will
OL,19,Fbring the proposition to the States.
